            . I am a <rs id="t18231203-28-viclabel153" type="occupation">seedsman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18231203-28-victim303 t18231203-28-viclabel153"></join>, and live in Tooley-street. On the 27th of October, about half-past four o'clock in the afternoon, I was on <placeName id="t18231203-28-crimeloc154">London-bridge</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18231203-28-crimeloc154" type="placeName" value="London-bridge"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18231203-28-crimeloc154" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18231203-28-off151 t18231203-28-crimeloc154"></join>, coming from the City - some waggons caused a stoppage. I felt a pressure at my coat pocket, turned round, and saw the prisoner with my handkerchief in his hand, and seized him. He said he had picked it up.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was going to Stockwell, and saw the handkerchief on the ground - I ran to pick it up, and before I could get to it, the gentleman collared me, and asked if I had a handkerchief; I said, No. He saw it on the ground, and picked it up. Two ladies told him I did not touch his pocket.</p>
